  {{property_address}}

  (the "Premises"), to be used solely as a private residential dwelling in the State of Kentucky.

  ----------------------------------------------------------

  2. LEASE TERM

  The lease term shall begin on {{lease_start_date}} and end on {{lease_end_date}}. This is a fixed-term tenancy.

  ----------------------------------------------------------

  3. RENT

  Tenant agrees to pay a monthly rent of {{monthly_rent}}, due on or before the 1st day of each calendar month, payable to Landlord at the address above or by any electronic method Landlord designates in writing.

  ----------------------------------------------------------

  4. LATE FEES

  Kentucky law provides a 5-day grace period before a late fee may be charged . A late fee of {{late_fee_flat}}, plus {{late_fee_daily}} per day for each additional day rent remains unpaid, shall apply after expiration of the grace period.

  ----------------------------------------------------------

  5. SECURITY DEPOSIT

  Tenant shall pay a security deposit of {{security_deposit}} prior to taking possession. Maximum allowed: no statutory cap (https://apps.legislature.ky.gov/law/statutes/statute.aspx?id=31581). Interest on deposit: No statutory interest requirement. The deposit shall be returned within 30 days after lease termination, less lawful deductions for unpaid rent, damages beyond ordinary wear and tear, and other permitted charges.

